The paper discusses the use of latent geometry notions to design dissimilarity matrices for community detection in complex networks using affinity propagation. This involves concepts related to network structure, machine learning, and data analysis, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) since the paper deals with community detection in networks. The second likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) since the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for clustering. The third likely category is cs.SD (Software Engineering) since the paper involves the development of algorithms for data analysis. The fourth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper deals with the design of dissimilarity matrices for clustering. The fifth likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) since the paper involves the analysis of network topology.
